posts.cooked: I’m trying to test my swerve code on our 2023 robot, I’m getting an error whenever I’m trying to deploy the code to the roboRIO, The error says that I have an Incompatible image on the roboRIO, I tried to imagine the roboRIO using the latest roboRIO image but It’s still 2023 image and not 2024, I reinstalled the FRC Game tools ( according to this ) and it didn’t helped

We downloaded the roborio 2 image from here and it seems to be working. It did take a while to download though. After you have to make sure to flash the image to the sd card and put it back in the rio and use a printer cable to connect it to the computer and then you can use the imaging tool. If you’re using the original just download the software from the link and use the imaging tool as normal.

posts.name: Thad House
posts.cooked: Click the Format Target circle. Then select the image and deploy it.

posts.name: James
posts.cooked:
Tried loading roborio firmware 2024.2

We get an error saying gradle version not compatible.  compatible versions 2024.2x ececpt for 2024.2

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: You’re likely running a beta version of WPILib.  You’ll want to update to the latest version (2024.2.1 at the moment).  Can be downloaded from the wpilib github releases page per the setup docs, same as if you were installing for the first time.

posts.name: Joe Ross
posts.cooked: I think it’s the opposite. I think they’re running the release WPILib with a roborio image from the beta. Need to install the release Game Tools (and probably uninstall the beta first).

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
Taking another look, yes, I think you’re right.  2024.0 was a beta release

OP, you’ll want to run the updated Game Tools installer to get the latest roborio image.  Then run the Roborio Imaging Tool to image the rio (image, not firmware) with the new image.  You’ll then need to deploy code again, but it should work this time.

posts.cooked: My team found it under format target or update firmware… one of the two, I forgot. Alternatively you can go through your frc game tool files and find it that way.

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
Firmware and image are different things.

There hasn’t been a necessary firmware update in several years now.

You can think of the image as the OS (because, well, it is).  It needs to be updated for each season (and sometimes multiple times during the season depending on issues being discovered and fixed).
